    Product Description

    You can fix it!

    Screens crack. Laptops slow. Batteries fail. Wear and tear is normal, but throwing away fixable stuff shouldn't be. Repair is better for your wallet and the environment. You dont need to be a Genius to fix your electronics. iFixit provides you with the right tools and multilingual repair guides.

    iFixit Essential Electronics Toolkit

    Everything you need to start your repair

    Broken displays and tired batteries can make your life quite difficult. But most repairs aren't that complicated - as long as you have the right tools at hand.

    If you're a DIY-enthusiast or a weekend warrior, this kit has what you need

    Our Essential Electronics Toolkit comes with everything you need for most electronics repairs. It also serves for tricky household repairs - whether it's repairing door handles, kitchen appliances or glasses - this toolkit is a good addition to your toolbox.

    Included in this kit:

    • Easy-to-open magnetized case made from recycled ABS with foam insert (Material: EVA)
    • Lid with built-in sorting tray
    • 4 mm bit driver - Ergonomic handle with magnetic bit socket, knurled grip, and swivel top with integrated SIM Eject Tool (Material: Polymer)
    • Angled tweezers - Tweezers with angled, pointed tips for hard-to-reach places
    • Spudger - Tool with pointed and flat ends for safely prying cables and sensitive electronics
    • Jimmy - Flexible steel blade with an ergonomic handle for precise and powerful prying
    • Opening Tool - Gets into the tightest cracks without scratching or marking your workpiece
    • 6 Opening Picks - Ultra-thin pick for slicing adhesive and separating screens and cases
    • Suction Handle -Light-duty suction cup for removing phone and tablet glass panels

    16 precision bits (4 mm) made of S2 steel:

    • Phillips - 000, 00, 0, 1, 2
    • Pentalobe - P2, P5
    • Flathead - 1, 2.5, 4 mm
    • Torx - T4, T5
    • Torx Security - TR6, TR8, TR10
    • Tri-Point - Y000

    Smart & Functional

    Whether it's a broken display, a battery replacement or the repair of a loose door handle - for always having the right tool at hand, we have combined the most important tools for you in this small but smart toolbox.

    • Here you'll find tools to safely open smartphones, laptops, as well as tools for gripping, holding, removing and installing even the smallest components. You also get a premium precision screwdriver and 16 precision bits, which serve for every basic electronic repair.
    • Everything is handy and well stored in the magnetic bit case. Thanks to a high-density foam insert, tools, components and bits can be safely stored and transported. Additionally, the inside of the lid serves as a sorting tray.

    Tools for opening, levering and prying

    To start your repair, you will need the right opening tools. With many modern devices, it is becoming increasingly difficult to open them. Our kit contains a well-thought-out selection of opening and prying tools, so you can open any case easily and safely.

    • Our specially developed suction lifter, for example, allows you to lift extremely sensitive or hard-to-grip components such as tablet and smartphone displays or touchscreens so that you can reach underneath them with the other opening and lever tools.
    • With the iFixit Jimmy, the famous iFixit Opening Tools, a Spudger and Opening Picks, you'll always have the right tool at hand - whether it's delicate components or tougher cases that require force.
    • Our Angled tweezers allow universal use and let you grip and hold even hard-to-reach device parts and sensitive cables.

    Precision Bit Driver with magnetic bit holder

    This bit driver made of high-quality Polymer enables precise work with a secure grip and is suitable for all 4 mm mini bits.

    • The solid handle is ergonomically shaped and knurled for easy operation.
    • The magnetic bit holder not only holds the, but also magnetises the bit, making it easier to work with tiny screws.
    • The swivel top allows you to turn endlessly until every screw is in place.

    16 Precision Bits (4 mm) made of high-quality S2 steel

    Electronics manufacturers often complicate repairs with individual screw profiles. This assortment of the 16 most important mini-bits puts an end to this.

    • You will find exactly the right bit for every profile: in addition to common types such as Flathead, Phillips and Torx, special bits such as Pentalobe (iPhone bit) are included.
    • Our precision bits are made of high-quality S2 steel. These precisely machined bits fit properly into the screws and protect both the bit and fasteners from damages
    • The necks of the bits are extra-long (15 mm), so that screwing in confined spaces is also possible.

    Please note: Our 4 mm bits are specially designed for precision mechanics, where precision is the primary concern, and are not intended for great force (as in furniture assembly).

    By the way: If the bits show any damage despite our checks, we will of course replace them free of charge.

    Right to repair

    You bought it. You own it.

    Once youve paid money for a product, the manufacturer shouldnt be able to dictate how you use it - its yours. Ownership means you should be able to open, hack, repair, upgrade, or tie bells on it. But its common practice to refuse to make parts, tools, and repair information available to consumers and small repair shops.

    Manufacturers have created a monopoly on repair

    When there's only one repair shop around, prices go up and quality goes down. Companies have every incentive to drive up prices and drive down competition. Dont let them. Become part of the iFixit community. Together we can fix the world!

    Save the environment

    We make a lot of e-waste

    When electronics end up in landfills, toxics like lead, mercury, and cadmium leach into the soil and water. The electronic waste problem is huge: More than 48 million tons of e-waste are produced every year. Even when recycled, a significant amount of electronic material cannot be recovered. Critical rare earths are present in every single electronic device you own. 99% of them cannot be recovered for recycling.

    High energy consumption, radioactive waste, destructive mining in informal mines where child labour and deaths of mine workers often occur, civil wars in Africa - mining and manufacturing is destruction. Making products last longer just makes sense - repair and reuse are our future. We need to make electronic products last longer. Repairing is sustainable, saves money and protects the environment. Every cell phone repaired is one less that needs to be manufactured. Fix your phone and your computer when they wear out.

    The iFixit-Community

    The easier it is to fix something, the more people do it. Help us teach people to make things last longer! On our website ifixit.com you can find lots of help and exchange ideas with other repair enthusiasts.

    Step-by-step instructions: Our thousands of step-by-step tutorials show you how to fix almost anything. They're free for everyone and available in many languages.

    Teardowns: Get a peek inside the latest gadgets with our user-generated teardowns.

    Forum: Q&A forum with more than 100,000 solved repair issues. Share your solutions with others or get advice if you need help.

    Community: A community of repair professionals from around the world sharing knowledge, tips and tricks. Get tips or teach others how to get their devices working again.

    Our products

    A complete repair solution from start to finish: in addition to our step-by-step instructions, you'll find everything else you need for your repair at iFixit:

    • High-quality precision tools designed specifically for electronics repair
    • Spare parts such as replacement batteries and displays for many devices from major manufacturers - smartphone, tablet, laptop or smartwatch
    • Functional repair kits for the every electronics repair, including all necessary tools to repair electronic devices

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.
